text: Gouda is a municipality in the province of South Holland, the Netherlands. In 2016 about 71,000 people lived there. The city is famous for its Gouda cheese and stroopwafels. The city hall was built in the 15th century. ==References== == Other websites == * * A collection of old pictures and drawings of Gouda. (A journey through the past) * *
title: Gouda, Netherlands
